51.4	Faisal_Shahzad	Faisal Shahzad	Faisal Shahzad (Urdu: ; born , 1979) is a Pakistani American who attempted the May 1, 2010, Times Square car bombing. On , 2010, in Federal District Court in Manhattan he confessed to 10 counts arising from the bombing attempt. Throughout his court appearance, Shahzad was unrepentant, and the United States attorney indicated there was no plea deal, so Shahzad faced the maximum sentence, a mandatory life term.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/83/Amd_mug_faisal-shahzad.jpg/220px-Amd_mug_faisal-shahzad.jpg
